description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have the unique skills and desire to manage our Regional Cardio-Thoracic Transplant Out-Patient Department one of only five units in England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly specialized individual who has the skills, motivation and patient centred approach, to manage and support our complex post heart and lung transplant patients. Who come from all over the North West of England, Wales, The Isle of Mann &amp; Northern Ireland living with a new organ &amp; helping them to transform their lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a senior nurse with proven leadership and cardio-thoracic transplant experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must posses the skills to work in this highly specialized area. Be passionate about delivering high standards of care with compassion. You will be rewarded by being part of something truly special. And supported to develop with a bespoke continuing professional development personal education plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameElaine BrazilJob titleMatron Cardiac Surgery &amp; TransplantEmail addresselaine.brazil@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 291 2090Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
